0. PREAMBLE — WHAT IS DISINFORMATION ARCHITECTURE?

Disinformation Architecture is the deliberate design of information systems
where multiple concurrent truths about the same entity may coexist without
collapse — not to deceive, but to make visible how placement, metadata,
collision, and register produce overlapping readings of content.

CIM (Conversation Entity Archive) practices Disinformation Architecture through:

  • neat stacking      — duplex-numeric fixed placement, mandatory register
  • cloud collision    — distributed services, metadata drift, ML rerank
  • .diff literacy     — reading divergence between layers as design material
  • serendipity links  — non-topical association across branches

This license governs the conceptual, curatorial, tutorial, and notational
layers of CIM. Software source code in this repository remains under MIT
License (see LICENSE) unless otherwise marked.

